headline: Tesla Offers Cut-Price New Vehicles In Europe, Trying to Arrest Sales Decline
summary: Tesla  has introduced its new “Standard” Model Y and Model 3 vehicles in Europe, hoping lower-priced versions of its two most popular cars can arrest sales declines in the region.  European websites for the electric vehicle maker now show lower-price versions of the Model 3 and Y that Tesla unveiled in the U.S. this past week.  Tesla could use the new options for European car buyers.
